{
  "_doc": [
    "Tests the effect of soft per-class data skew. Each user has a data_percent plus a per-label",
    "retention factor: 1.0 keeps the full fair share, 0.6 keeps 60%. Example: 10% data_percent",
    "with retention 1.0 on label 1 -> 10% of label 1 in the dataset; retention 0.6 -> 6%.",
    "Expectation: users with stronger data coverage on a dataset perform better and earn a higher",
    "reputation score. Label distributions are intentionally skewed, but softened compared with",
    "earlier hard-skew presets."
  ],
